@zhztheplayer , I'm afraid I have no clue here, so you can disregard my comments.

I'm puzzled how even LogicalProject collation could work. Current collation for Project takes the value from its input, thus it basically forces each and every Project implementation to keep order of the rows which might easily break in case the project is performed via multithreaded algorithm.

I've no idea whether collation should be defined at LogicalWindow level, at EnumerableWindow level or for both of them.
